content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

To create a flyout:

In your org, click the App Launcher, click Vlocity Cards, and click New to create a new card layout.
On the New Layout screen, in the Type field, select Flyout.

Select the flyout Data Source:

To use the parent context variable of the card layout where you'll add your flyout, select Parent as the data source. To display specific data in the flyout:

Click View Data on the Layout or Card pane and copy the JSON data by clicking Copy to clipboard.
Choose Sample as the Data Source and paste the copied JSON inside the input field.

From the Fields picklist, add data fields.

If your flyout does not use data from the parent context variable of the card layout, add a data source to the layout.

Click Activate on the Layout pane and on each card.

Add a flyout to a card state to display additional information about the record displayed on the card when you click the card.
title: Creating a Flyout in OmniStudio
